To assign a role based on an emoji reaction in Discord.js, you can use the following code:

```js
//Define reaction roles
const reactionRoles = {
  '🍎': 'apple',
  '🍊': 'orange',
  '🍇': 'grape',
  //add more emoji-role pairs as needed
};

//listen for reactions
client.on('messageReactionAdd', async (reaction, user) => {
  //check if the reaction is from a bot
  if (user.bot) return;

  //check if the reaction is in the reaction roles object
  if (reaction.emoji.name in reactionRoles) {
    //get the role object based on the reaction
    let role = reaction.message.guild.roles.cache.find(role => role.name.toLowerCase() === reactionRoles[reaction.emoji.name]);

    //check if role exists
    if (role) {
      //add role to user
      let member = await reaction.message.guild.members.fetch(user.id);
      member.roles.add(role);
    }
  }
});

//listen for reaction removals
client.on('messageReactionRemove', async (reaction, user) => {
  //check if the reaction is from a bot
  if (user.bot) return;

  //check if the reaction is in the reaction roles object
  if (reaction.emoji.name in reactionRoles) {
    //get the role object based on the reaction
    let role = reaction.message.guild.roles.cache.find(role => role.name.toLowerCase() === reactionRoles[reaction.emoji.name]);

    //check if role exists
    if (role) {
      //remove role from user
      let member = await reaction.message.guild.members.fetch(user.id);
      member.roles.remove(role);
    }
  }
});
```

In this code, we define an object called `reactionRoles` that maps each emoji to a role name. We then listen for `messageReactionAdd` and `messageReactionRemove` events to check if the reaction is in the `reactionRoles` object and assign or remove the corresponding role to/from the user based on the emoji they reacted with. We also check if the user is a bot to prevent the bot from assigning roles to itself. 

Note: This code assumes that the bot has the necessary permissions to assign and remove roles.

